
 The program stores attendance and marks of 5 students using 2D arrays.

 It takes input for names, attendance (0/1), and marks (0â€“100).

 It calculates total attendance, absences, total marks, averages, topper, and lowest performer.

 A menu using loops and switch-case displays reports like attendance, marks, performance, and grades.
 The program helps beginners understand arrays, loops, and basic data analysis in C.
